{"cursor":"7065","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"'Equity sharing', also known as 'shared ownership' or in the US as 'housing\nequity partnership' (HEP), allows a person to purchase a share in their home\neven if they cannot afford a mortgage on the whole of the current value. It is\ngenerally used in affordable housing, providing a \"third way\" of land tenure\nbetween home ownership and renting.\n\nThe remaining equity share may be held by the housebuilder, by a private\ninvestor or by a landlord such as a housing association. In some models the\nresident pays rent on that share.\n","linknr":126,"url":"Housing_equity_partnership","recorded":1364190852,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Equity_sharing&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Equity_sharing&action=edit","//en.wikipedia.org/apple-touch-icon.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","/wiki/Equity_sharing","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.wikihiero%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","/w/index.php?title=Housing_equity_partnership&redirect=no","#mw-head","#p-search","/wiki/Mortgage_loan","/wiki/Affordable_housing","/wiki/Land_tenure","/wiki/Real_estate_development","/wiki/Housing_association","/wiki/Renting","#Types_of_equity_sharing","#Equity_sharing_in_different_countires","#United_States","#United_Kingdom","#England","#Private_sector_shared_equity","#See_also","#References